s%20month's%20Fed%20policy%20meeting%2C%20and%20that%20the%20benchmark%20rate%20will%20likely%20stay%20in%20the%20current%205.25%25-5.50%25%20range%20through%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20economy%20can%20continue%20to%20expand%20and%20the%20labor%20market%20can%20cool%20at%20a%20slow%20pace%2C%20rather%20than%20at%20a%20rapid%20clip%2C%20then%20the%20Fed%20can%20afford%20to%20leave%20rates%20where%20they%20are%20and%20patiently%20wait%20for%20(current)%20higher%20rates%20to%20do%20their%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20Chris%20Zaccarelli%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20trades%20were%20lower%20for%20the%20day%2C%20each%20major%20index%20gained%20through%20August's%20closing%20week.%20The%20tech-heavy%20Nasdaq%20gained%20about%203%25%2C%20followed%20by%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20at%202%25%20and%20Dow%20at%201%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHere's%20where%20US%20indexes%20stood%20shortly%20after%20the%204%3A00%20p.m.%20closing%20bell%20on%20Friday%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Findex%2Fs%26amp%3Bp_500%3Futm_source%3Dmarkets%26utm_medium%3Dingest%253Futm_source%253Dmarkets%26utm_medium%3Dingest%26utm_medium%3Dingest%26utm_source%3Dmarkets%26utm_medium%3Dingest%26utm_source%3Dmarkets%26utm_medium%3Dingest%26utm_source%3Dmarkets%5C%22%3ES%26amp%3BP%20500%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%204%2C515.77%2C%20up%200.18%25%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Findex%2Fdow_jones%3Futm_source%3Dmarkets%26utm_medium%3Dingest%253Futm_source%253Dmarkets%26utm_medium%3Dingest%26utm_medium%3Dingest%26utm_source%3Dmarkets%26utm_medium%3Dingest%26utm_source%3Dmarkets%26utm_medium%3Dingest%26utm_source%3Dmarkets%5C%22%3EDow%20Jones%20Industrial%20Average%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%2034%2C838.01%2C%20up%200.33%25%20(%2B116.10%20points)%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%