-war-drone-strikes-shut-down-moscow-airports-again-2023-8%5C%22%3Eroutinely%3C%2Fa%3E%20targeted%20by%20unmanned%20aerial%20vehicles.%20Unlike%20some%20of%20the%20other%20attacks%2C%20these%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20cause%20psychological%20harm%20than%20actual%20physical%20damage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224972%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Russian%20II-76%20transport%20plane%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f13ad657bff700194824e7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222845%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Russian%20Il-76%20MD%20airlifter%20is%20seen%20during%20the%202021%20International%20Army%20Games%20at%20the%20Alabino%20training%20ground%20on%20August%2023%2C%202021%20in%20Moscow%20Region%2C%20Russia.%3Cp%3EPhoto%20by%20Wang%20Xiujun%2FChina%20News%20Service%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20frequent%20strikes%20highlight%20a%20problem%20for%20Russia's%20air%20defenses%2C%20the%20British%20defense%20ministry%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMany%20of%20these%20UAVs%20have%20reached%20their%20targets%2C%20which%20likely%20means%20that%20Russian%20air%20defense%20is%20having%20difficulty%20detecting%20and%20destroying%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20UK%20said%20in%20its%20intelligence%20update.%20%26quot%3BRussia%20is%20likely%20rethinking%20its%20air%20defense%20posture%20in%20the%20area%20between%20Ukraine%20and%20Moscow%20to%20better%20deal%20with%20these%20attacks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20UK%20said%20the%20Pskov%20attack%20indicated%20that%20Ukraine's%20drones%20have%20a%20far%20reach%2C%20given%20that%20the%20base%20is%20situated%20hundreds%20of%20miles%20from%20Ukrainian%20territory%2C%20but%C2%A0considering%20Budanov's%20comments%20about%20the%20job%20having%20been%20carried%20out%20from%20within%20Russia%2C%20it's%20unclear%20how%20far%20these%20specific%20drones%20traveled%20before%20they%20reached%20the%20base.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20