%3Cfigcaption%3ESen.%20Elizabeth%20Warren%20has%20called%20Corizon%20Health's%20bankruptcy%20maneuver%20%26quot%3Ba%20red%20flag.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ELeigh%20Vogel%2FGetty%20Images%20for%20Caring%20Across%20Generations%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ELeading%20prison%20health%20provider%20Corizon%20Health%20split%20last%20year%20and%20filed%20one%20company%2C%20called%20Tehum%2C%20into%20bankruptcy%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESources%20tell%20Insider%20the%20parties%20reached%20a%20tentative%20settlement%20of%20%2430%20million%2C%20a%20small%20fraction%20of%20the%20company's%20debt%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThat%20deal%20could%20leave%20hospitals%20and%20hundreds%20of%20prisoners%20who%20claim%20they%20were%20harmed%20by%20Corizon%20with%20tiny%20settlements%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESen.%20Elizabeth%20Warren%20is%20now%20looking%20into%20Corizon's%20use%20of%20a%20controversial%20legal%20maneuver%20called%20the%20Texas%20Two-Step%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ECorizon%20Health%2C%20once%20the%20nation's%20largest%20prison%20healthcare%20provider%2C%20reached%20a%20tentative%20bankruptcy%20deal%20last%20week%20that%20could%20leave%20hundreds%20of%20prisoners%20with%20pennies%20on%20the%20dollar%20for%20their%20medical%20malpractice%20claims.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20settlement%20is%20approved%2C%20it%20would%20mean%20that%20Corizon's%20owners%20succeeded%20in%20their%20use%20of%20a%20controversial%20financial%20maneuver%20called%20the%20Texas%20Two-Step.%20In%20a%20recent%20civil%20complaint%2C%20Isaac%20Lefkowitz%2C%20a%20company%20representative%2C%20said%20the%20Two-Step%20is%20used%20to%20%26quot%3Bforce%20plaintiffs%20into%20accepting%20lower%20payments.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESen.%20Elizabeth%20Warren%20has%20called%20Corizon's%20use%20of%20the%20Two-Step%20%26quot%3Ban%20alarming%20red%20flag.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20two%20people%20close%20to%20the%20negotiations%2C%20the%20settlement%20figure%20is%20around%20%2430%20million.%20The%20amount%20could%20still%20change%20as%20the%20agreement%20is%20made%20final.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPriority%20claims%2C%20such%20as%20attorney's%20fees%2C%20would%20be%20paid%20out%20first.%20One%20of%20the%20sources%20said%20those%20fees%20may%20be%20roughly%20%249%20million%2C%20which%20would%20leave%20around%20%2420%20million%20for%20all%20the%20other%20creditor%20claims.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECorizon%20Health%20rebranded%20as%20Tehum%20Care%20Services%20last%20year%20and%20filed%20for%20bankruptcy%20in%20February.%20As%20of%20July%2C%20Tehum%20faced%20at%20least%20%2488%20million%20in%20claims%20over%20unpaid%20invoices%20from%20medical%20providers%20and%2044%20employment-law%20suits%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20at%20least%20475%20lawsuits%20filed%20by%20current%20and%20former%20prisoners%20and%20their%20families%20alleging%20negligent%20care.%20These%20include%20suits%20filed%20by%20William%20Kelly%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23909384-william-kelly-complaint%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclaimed%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20his%20kidney%20cancer%20progressed%20to%20stage%204%20while%20he%20was%20under%20Corizon's%20care%20in%20Michigan%20prisons%3B%20Tracey%20Grissom%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.courtlistener.com%2Frecap%2Fgov.uscourts.almd.70032%2Fgov.uscourts.almd.70032.1.0.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efiled%20suit%20in%202019%3C%2Fa%3E%20saying%20that%20Corizon's%20failure%20to%20provide%20a%20properly%20fitted%20ostomy%20bag%20at%20the%20Alabama%20prison%20where%20she%20was%20held%20forced%20her%20to%20live%20in%20her%20own%20feces%20for%20four%20months%3B%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23909382-hector-garcia-jr-amended-complaint%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efamily%20of%20Hector%20Garcia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20died%20after%20being%20under%20Corizon's%20care%20for%20only%20a%20few%20days%20in%20New%20Mexico.%20(Corizon%20has%20disputed%20all%20three%20claims%20in%20court%3B%20attorneys%20say%20it's%20unclear%20whether%20the%20bankruptcy%20deal%20will%20release%20other%20defendants%20in%20the%20475%20cases.)%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222743%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22William%20Kelly%20sits%20on%20a%20couch%20in%20his%20home%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f1240a57bff70019481fdd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWilliam%20Kelly%2C%20of%20Saginaw%2C%20Michigan%2C%20has%20kidney%20cancer%20that%20progressed%20to%20stage%204%20while%20he%20was%20under%20the%20care%20of%20Corizon%20Health%20in%20Michigan%20prisons.%20He's%20one%20of%20at%20least%20475%20people%20with%20active%20suits%20against%20Corizon%20claiming%20negligent%20care.%3Cp%3ESylvia%20Jarrus%20for%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20total%2C%20Tehum%20has%20reported%20%24176%20million%20in%20unsecured%20debt%20it%20seeks%20to%20resolve%20with%20the%20settlement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETehum%20and%20a%20committee%20representing%20the%20creditors%20agreed%20to%20mediation%20in%20May%20in%20an%20order%20signed%20by%20US%20Bankruptcy%20Judge%20Christopher%20Lopez%2C%20who%20is%20overseeing%20the%20bankruptcy%20case%20for%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20Texas.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20Friday%2C%20after%20three%20days%20of%20mediation%20talks%2C%20Aaron%20Kaufman%2C%20an%20attorney%20representing%20Tehum%2C%20told%20the%20court%20that%20Tehum%20and%20its%20creditors'%20committee%20had%20reached%20a%20preliminary%20settlement%20that%20would%20%26quot%3Bresolve%20all%20disputes%20among%20the%20debtor%20and%20the%20mediation%20parties.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKaufman%20declined%20to%20provide%20any%20details%20about%20the%20settlement%20in%20court%2C%20saying%20they%20would%20be%20shared%20in%20the%20coming%20weeks%20when%20Tehum%20files%20a%20detailed%20liquidation%20plan.%20He%20also%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20record%20to%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Texas%20Two-Step%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcorizon-health-bankruptcy-yescare-texas-two-step-law-2023-8%5C%22%3EInsider%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20settlement%20is%20the%20end%20game%20in%20Corizon's%20Texas%20Two-Step%2C%20a%20controversial%20legal%20maneuver%20the%20company%20employed%20to%20wall%20off%20most%20of%20its%20assets%20from%20these%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20Corizon%20moved%20its%20incorporation%20from%20Delaware%20to%20Texas%2C%20where%20state%20law%20permits%20something%20called%20a%20divisional%20merger%2C%20allowing%20companies%20to%20split%20in%20two%2C%20keeping%20most%20assets%20with%20one%20company%20and%20consigning%20most%20debts%20to%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECorizon%20gave%20one%20company%2C%20known%20as%20YesCare%2C%20all%20of%20Corizon's%20active%20contracts%20with%20state%20and%20local%20governments%2C%20worth%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars.%20Two%20months%20later%2C%20YesCare%20won%20a%20new%20multiyear%20contract%20for%20more%20than%20%241%20billion%20to%20provide%20healthcare%20to%20prisoners%20held%20by%20the%20Alabama%20Department%20of%20Corrections.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20company%2C%20Corizon%2C%20later%20rebranded%20as%20Tehum%2C%20received%20most%20of%20the%20parent%20company's%20liabilities%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20declared%20bankruptcy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESen.%20Elizabeth%20Warren%20is%20examining%20Corizon's%20use%20of%20the%20Two-Step%20following%20Insider's%20reporting%2C%20according%20to%20spokesperson%20Alex%20Sarabia.%20Insider%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcorizon-health-bankruptcy-yescare-texas-two-step-law-2023-8%5C%22%3Euncovered%20evidence%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Corizon's%20new%20owners%2C%20who%20purchased%20the%20company%20in%20December%202021%2C%20had%20engaged%20in%20extensive%20self-dealing%2C%20sending%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20to%20companies%20they%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWarren%20is%20%26quot%3Bactively%20looking%26quot%3B%20into%20the%20Corizon%20Two-Step%2C%20Sarabia%20confirmed%20last%20week%2C%20before%20the%20settlement%20was%20announced.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20expect%20future%20congressional%20oversight%20led%20by%20Senator%20Warren's%20office.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20court%2C%20Kaufman%2C%20the%20Tehum%20attorney%2C%20blamed%20Insider's%20reporting%20for%20the%20company's%20decision%20to%20to%20keep%20the%20details%20of%20the%20settlement%20secret.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20want%20our%20process%20derailed%20by%20misstatements%20about%20what%20the%20terms%20are%20or%20how%20they%20impact%20creditors%20or%20we%20don't%20want%20creditors%20pre-judging%20the%20plan%20before%20it's%20even%20filed%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20rushed%20timeline%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20creditors%20have%20worried%20for%20months%20that%20the%20company%20would%20reach%20a%20settlement%20on%20unfavorable%20terms.%20In%20June%2C%20several%20creditors%20filed%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kccllc.net%2Ftehum%2Fdocument%2F2390086230630000000000003%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20motion%3C%2Fa%3E%20asking%20the%20court%20to%20appoint%20an%20independent%20trustee%20to%20oversee%20Tehum%2C%20arguing%20that%20the%20self-dealing%20by%20Tehum%20was%20tantamount%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bfraudulent%20transfer%26quot%3B%20of%20assets%20outside%20the%20reach%20of%20the%20creditors.%20They%20want%20the%20Two-Step%20unwound%20or%20YesCare's%20assets%20to%20be%20consolidated%20with%20Tehum's%20so%20there's%20more%20money%20available%20to%20pay%20creditors.%20A%20heari