s%20against%20Navlakha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20may%20have%20our%20own%20reservations%2C%20prima%20facie%2C%20but%20we%20will%20not%20say%20anything.%20Quite%20a%20lengthy%20order%20was%20passed.%20But%20without%20getting%20into%20merits%20if%20such%20an%20order%20is%20made%20applicable%20to%20everyone%20then%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Justice%20Sundresh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20previous%20order%20was%20passed%20by%20another%20bench%20of%20the%20top%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20made%20these%20remarks%20while%20hearing%20an%20application%20filed%20by%20Navlakha%20to%20change%20his%20address%2C%20in%20view%20of%20the%20earlier%20order%20for%20his%20house%20arrest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20National%20Investigation%20Agency%20(NIA)%20argued%20that%20the%20house%20arrest%20was%20unwarranted%20and%20that%20Navlakha%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20paid%20a%20portion%20of%20his%20security%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20central%20probe%20agency%20said%20that%20he%20is%20yet%20to%20pay%20up%20at%20least%2025%25%20of%20the%20dues%20to%20cover%20the%20expenses%20of%20his%20security%20cover%2C%20which%20amounted%20to%20Rs%201.1%20crore%2C%20according%20to%20the%20local%20police.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Nitya%20Ramakrishnan%2C%20representing%20Navlakha%2C%20refuted%20the%20allegation%20and%20pointed%20out%20that%20no%20break-up%20of%20such%20dues%20has%20been%20provided.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20adjourned%20the%20matter%20for%20eight%20weeks%2C%20allowing%20both%20parties%20to%20submit%20their%20responses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-test-id%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20apex%20court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-allows-gautam-navlakha-to-be-moved-to-house-arrest%5C%22%3Ehad%20on%20November%2010%20allowed%20Navlakha%20to%20be%20placed%20under%20house%20arrest%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20account%20of%20his%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20NIA%20had%20requested%20that%20Navlakha%E2%80%99s%20transfer%20from%20prison%20to%20house%20arrest%20be%20put%20on%20hold%2C%20raising%20concerns%20about%20the%20security%20of%20the%20premises.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavlakha%20had%20been%20arrested%20in%20August%202018.%20The%20case%20relates%20to%20alleged%20inflammatory%20speeches%20made%20at%20the%20%E2%80%98Elgar%20Parishad%E2%80%99%20conclave%20held%20in%20Pune%20on%20December%2031%2C%202017%2C%20which%20Pune%20police%20claimed%20triggered%20violence%20the%20next%20day%20near%20the%20Koregaon%20Bhima%20war%20memorial%20on%20the%20outskirts%20of%20the%20western%20Maharashtra%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Pune%20police%20had%20claimed%20the%20conclave%20was%20backed%20by%20Maoists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20was%20later%20handed%20over%20to%20the%20NIA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693575497000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25222448%2FSupreme-Court-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-expresses-doubt-on-gautam-navlakhas-jail-to-house-arrest-decision-in-bhima-koregaon-case%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20bench%20of%20Justices%20M.M.%20Sundresh%20and%20J.B.%20Pardiwala%20noted%20that%20the%20order%20did%20not%20deal%20with%20the%20merits%20of%20the%20overall%20case%20and%20proceedings%20against%20Navlakha.%20The%20previous%20order%20was%20passed%20by%20another%20bench%20of%20the%20top%20court.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-expresses-doubt-on-gautam-navlakhas-jail-to-house-arrest-decision-in-bhima-koregaon-case%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'KN%20Singh%20had%20lost%20vision%20in%20both%20eyes'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693574936000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%