ttps%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F07%2FMadras_High_Court_PTI.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Madras%20high%20court%20has%20come%20down%20heavily%20on%20the%20Directorate%20of%20Vigilance%20and%20Anti-corruption%20(DVAC)%2C%20calling%20it%20a%20%E2%80%9Cchameleon%E2%80%9D%20changing%20colours%20depending%20on%20which%20political%20party%20is%20in%20power%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Ftamil-nadu%2Fdvac-has-become-a-chameleon-says-madras-hc-as-it-takes-suo-motu-revision-of-ops-case-2667894%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20made%20the%20comments%20on%20Thursday%2C%20August%2031%2C%20after%20deciding%20to%20take%20suo%20motu%20revision%20of%20a%202012%20local%20court%20order%20that%20had%20permitted%20DVAC%20to%20withdraw%20a%20disproportionate%20assets%20(DA)%20case%20against%20former%20chief%20minister%20O.%20Panneerselvam%2C%20a%20year%20after%20his%20All%20India%20Anna%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%20(AIADMK)%20party%20came%20to%20power%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Anand%20Venkatesh%20has%20also%20decided%20to%20review%20the%20local%20court%20order%20of%202012%20which%20had%20also%20discharged%20three%20Dravid%20Muuentra%20Kazhagam%20(DMK)%20ministers%20K.%20Ponmudy%2C%20K.K.%20S.S.R.%20Ramachandran%2C%20and%20Thangam%20Thennarasu%20from%20disproportionate%20asset%20cases%20along%20with%20Pannerselvam.%20Tamil%20Nadu%E2%80%99s%20anti-corruption%20watchdog%2C%20DVAC%2C%20had%20filed%20the%20case%20against%20Pannerselvam%20in%202006%2C%20and%20the%20charge%20sheet%20in%20the%20case%20was%20filed%20in%202009%20after%20the%20DMK%20came%20to%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStating%20that%20DVAC%20has%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20a%20%E2%80%9Cchameleon%E2%80%9D%2C%20Justice%20Venkatesh%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CUnfortunately%2C%20courts%20have%20also%20acted%20in%20tandem%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20court%20will%20be%20failing%20in%20its%20constitutional%20duty%20if%20it%20%E2%80%9Ccloses%20its%20eyes%20to%20such%20systemic%20failure%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20fourth%20time%20in%20a%20month%20that%20the%20high%20court%20has%20pulled%20up%20DVAC.%20Last%20week%2C%20the%20high%20court%20had%20said%20%E2%80%9Csomething%20is%20very%20rotten%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20Special%20Court%20for%20MP%2FMLA%20Cases%20at%20Sriviliputhur%2C%20while%20taking%20up%20suo%20motu%20revision%20of%20cases%20involving%20Ramachandran%20and%20Thennarasu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EComing%20down%20heavily%20on%20the%20DVAC%20officials%2C%20the%20judge%20observed%20that%20they%20had%20changed%20their%20stance%20after%202021%2C%20the%20year%20when%20the%20DMK%20assumed%20power%20after%20defeating%20AIADMK%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693557047000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F07%2FMadras_High_Court_PTI.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fmadras-hc-pulls-up-tn-anti-corruption-watchdog-for-changing-stance-as-per-party-in-power%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20court%20described%20the%20Directorate%20of%20Vigilance%20and%20Anti-corruption%20a%20'chameleon'%20changing%20colours%20to%20suit%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20governing%20party.%20It%20made%20the%20remarks%20after%20deciding%20to%20review%20a%202012%20local%20court%20order%20which%20withdrew%20a%20disproportionate%20assets%20case%20against%20former%20CM%20Pannerselvam.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fmadras-hc-pulls-up-tn-anti-corruption-watchdog-for-changing-stance-as-per-party-in-power%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Legionnaires'%20disease%20has%20killed%2016%20people%20in%20Poland%20and%20been%20found%20on%20the%20asylum%20seeker%20barge%20-%20but%20what%20is