al%20landscape%20in%20the%20last%20several%20years%2C%20creating%20a%20sense%20of%20disquiet%2C%20has%20gathered%20storm%20in%20the%20past%20six%20months.%20After%20all%2C%20there%20is%20a%20line-up%20of%20state%20assembly%20elections%20before%20the%20nation%20goes%20to%20the%20polls%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20on%20March%202%2C%202023%2C%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2015%2F1458%2F1458_2015_3_1501_42634_Judgement_02-Mar-2023.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAnoop%20Baranwal%20vs%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20directed%20that%20the%20appointments%20of%20the%20CEC%20and%20the%20ECs%20%E2%80%9Cshall%20be%20done%20by%20the%20President%20of%20India%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20advice%20tendered%20by%20a%20Committee%20consisting%20of%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20of%20India%2C%20the%20Leader%20of%20the%20Opposition%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%2C%20in%20case%2C%20there%20is%20no%20such%20Leader%2C%20the%20Leader%20of%20the%20largest%20Party%20in%20the%20Opposition%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20having%20the%20largest%20numerical%20strength%2C%20and%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India.%20This%20norm%20will%20continue%20to%20hold%20good%20till%20a%20law%20is%20made%20by%20the%20Parliament.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20August%2010%2C%202023%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20introduced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Ffiles%2Fbills_acts%2Fbills_parliament%2F2023%2FBill_Text_Chief_Election_Commissioner_and_other_Election_Commissioners_Bill_2023.pdf%5C%22%3EThe%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20other%20Election%20Commissioners%20(Appointment%2C%20Conditions%20of%20Service%20and%20Terms%20of%20Office)%20Bill%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20saying%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20that%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20other%20Election%20Commissioners%20shall%20be%20appointed%20by%20the%20President%20on%20the%20recommendation%20of%20a%20Selection%20Committee%20consisting%20of%E2%80%94%20(a)%20the%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%94Chairperson%3B%20(b)%20the%20Leader%20of%20Opposition%20in%20the%20House%20of%20the%20People%E2%80%94Member%3B%20(c)%20a%20Union%20Cabinet%20Minister%20to%20be%20nominated%20by%20the%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%94Member.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20sequence%20of%20events%20has%20fuelled%20an%20animated%20debate%20among%20legal%20scholars%2C%20former%20CECs%2C%20civil%20servants%20and%20civil%20society%20organisations%20in%20the%20public%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20a%20clear%2C%20unambiguous%20assessment%20of%20the%20Bill%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20judgment%20would%20help%20foreground%20the%20nuances%20of%20the%20issue%20at%20stake%2C%20the%20fact%20is%20that%20appointments%20to%20the%20ECI%20are%20so%20crucial%20that%20we%20need%20to%20look%20beyond%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%20and%20the%20Bill%20for%20a%20fresh%20perspective.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJudgments%20of%20the%20higher%20judiciary%20typically%20comprise%20several%20major%20segments.%20They%20begin%20with%20what%20can%20broadly%20be%20referred%20to%20as%20the%20facts%20of%20the%20case%20%E2%80%93%20the%20historical%20or%20contextual%20background%2C%20a%20summary%20of%20relevant%20laws%20including%20those%20presented%20by%20the%20opposing%20counsel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20come%20the%20critical%20components%2C%20sometimes%20partly%20overlapping%20with%20the%20facts%20of%20the%20case%2C%20namely%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3Edirection(s)%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20the%20%3Cem%3Eratio%20decidendi%20(%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20legal%20principle%20or%20rationale%20for%20the%20decision)%2C%20which%20are%20essential.%20(The%20other%20component%2C%20%3Cem%3Eobiter%20dicta%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Eor%20that%20which%20is%20said%20in%20passing%20by%20the%20judge%2C%20is%20not%20essential%20to%20the%20ruling.)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%C2%A0rationale%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20ruling%2C%20reproduced%20above%2C%20is%20excerpted%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felection-commissioners-appointment-bill-farewell-to-free-and-fair-elections%5C%22%3Epara%20125%20of%20Justice%20Ajay%20Rastogi%E2%80%99s%20concurring%20judgment%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CKeeping%20in%20view%20the%20importance%20of%20maintaining%20the%20neutrality%20and%20independence%20of%20the%20office%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20to%20hold%20free%20and%20fair%20election%20which%20is%20a%20sine%20qua%20non%20for%20upholding%20the%20democracy%20as%20enshrined%20in%20our%20Constitution%2C%20it%20becomes%20imperative%20to%20shield%20the%20appointment%20of%20Election%20Commissioners%20and%20to%20be%20insulated%20from%20the%20executive%20interference%E2%80%A6.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0In%20the%20main%20judgment%2C%20Justice%20K.M.%20Joseph%2C%20speaking%20for%20himself%2C%20Justice%20Aniruddha%20Bose%2C%20Justice%20Hrishikesh%20Roy%2C%20and%20Justice%20C.T.%20Ravikumar%2C%20writes%20a%20separate%20section%20titled%20%E2%80%98Independence%3A%20a%20sterling%20and%20indispensable%20attribute.%E2%80%99%20This%20section%2C%20which%20forms%20the%20crux%20of%20the%20rationale%20for%20the%20entire%20judgment%2C%20deserves%20to%20be%20quoted%20at%20some%20length%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhat%20is%20independence%3F%20Independence%20is%20a%20value%2C%20which%20is%20only%20one%20of%20the%20elements%20in%20the%20amalgam%20of%20virtues%20that%20a%20person%20should%20possess.%20The%20competence%20of%20a%20man%20is%20not%20to%20be%20conflated%20with%20fierce%20independence.%20A%20person%20may%20be%20excellent%2C%20i.e.%2C%20at%20his%20chosen%20vocation.%20He%20may%20be%20an%20excellent%20Administrator.%20He%20may%20be%20honest%20but%20the%20quality%20of%20independence%20transcends%20the%20contours%20of%20the%20qualities%20of%20professional%20excellence%2C%20as%20also%20the%20dictates%20of%20honesty.%20We%20may%2C%20no%20doubt%2C%20clarify%20that%2C%20ordinarily%2C%20honesty%20would%20embrace%20the%20quality%20of%20courage%20of%20conviction%2C%20flowing%20from%20the%20perception%20of%20what%20is%20right%20and%20what%20is%20wrong.%20%3Cem%3EIrrespective%20of%20consequences%20to%20the%20individual%2C%20an%20honest%20person%20would%2C%20ordinarily%2C%20unrelentingly%20take%20on%20the%20high%20and%20mighty%20and%20persevere%20in%20the%20righteous%20path.%20An%20Election%20Commissioner%20is%20answerable%20to%20the%20Nation.%20The%20people%20of%20the%20country%20look%20forward%20to%20him%20so%20that%20democracy%20is%20always%20preserved%20and%20fostered.%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%20Independence%20must%20be%20related%2C%20finally%2C%20to%20the%20question%20of%20%E2%80%98what%20is%20right%20and%20what%20is%20wrong%E2%80%99.%20A%20person%2C%20who%20is%20weak%20kneed%20before%20the%20powers%20that%20be%2C%20cannot%20be%20appointed%20as%20an%20Election%20Commissioner.%20A%20person%2C%20who%20is%20in%20a%20state%20of%20obligation%20or%20feels%20indebted%20to%20the%20one%20who%20appointed%20him%2C%20fails%20the%20nation%20and%20can%20have%20no%20place%20in%20the%20conduct%20of%20elections%2C%20forming%20the%20very%20foundation%20of%20the%20democracy.%20An%20independent%20person%20cannot%20be%20biased.%20Holding%20the%20scales%20evenly%2C%20even%20in%20the%20stormiest%20of%20times%2C%20not%20being%20servile%20to%20the%20powerful%2C%20but%20coming%20to%20the%20rescue%20of%20the%20weak%20and%20the%20wronged%2C%20who%20are%20otherwise%20in%20the%20right%2C%20would%20qualify%20as%20true%20independence.%20Upholding%20the%20constitutional%20values%2C%20which%20are%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20a%20part%20of%20the%20Basic%20Structure%2C%20and%20which%20includes%2C%20democracy%2C%20the%20Rule%20of%20Law%2C%20the%20Right%20to%20Equality%2C%20secularism%20and%20the%20purity%20of%20elections%E2%80%A6%20would%2C%20indeed%2C%20proclaim%20the%20presence%20of%20independence.%20Independence%20must%20embrace%20the%20ability%20to%20be%20firm%2C%20even%20as%20against%20the%20highest%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Not%20unnaturally%2C%20uncompromising%20fearlessness%20will%20mark%20an%20independent%20person%20from%20those%20who%20put%20all%20they%20hold%20dear%20before%20their%20Karma.%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIt%20is%20important%20that%20the%20appointment%20must%20not%20be%20overshadowed%20by%20even%20a%20perception%2C%20that%20a%20%E2%80%98yes%20man%E2%80%99%20will%20decide%20the%20fate%20of%20democracy%20and%20all%20that%20it%20promises%20%3C%2Fem%3E(emphasis%20added)%3Cem%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20essence%20of%20the%20rationale%20for%20the%20decision%20of%20this%20judgment%2C%20therefore%20is%20independence%20of%20Election%20Commissioners%20and%20their%20insulation%20from%20executive%20interference.%20Independence%2C%20in%20this%20context%2C%20%E2%80%9Cmust%20embrace%20the%20ability%20to%20be%20firm%2C%20even%20as%20%5Bsic%5D%20against%20the%20highest%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EWatch%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Watch%20%7C%20'Modi%20Govt's%20EC%20Bill%20Undermines%20Its%20Independence%2C%20Should%20Be%20Struck%20Down%20if%20Passed'%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fvideo-karan-thapar-election-commission-gautam-bhatia%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Modi%20Govt%E2%80%99s%20EC%20Bill%20Undermines%20Its%20Independence%2C%20Should%20Be%20Struck%20Down%20if%20Passed%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20far%20does%20the%20Bill%20follow%20the%20rationale%20of%20SC%20ruling%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EA%20%3C%2Fem%3Equick%20look%20at%20the%20table%20below%20is%20sufficient%20to%20show%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20The%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20other%20Election%20Commissioners%20(Appointment%2C%20Conditions%20of%20Service%20and%20Terms%20of%20Office)%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20follows%20the%20rationale%20anchoring%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ruling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2266%5C%22%3ESection%20No.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22331%5C%22%3EDescription%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22104%5C%22%3ESupports%20independence%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22101%5C%22%3EReduces%20independence%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2266%5C%22%3E5%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22331%5C%22%3EOnly%20current%20and%20former%20secretaries%20to%20the%20Government%20of%20India%2C%20who%20are%20persons%20of%20integrity%2C%20who%20have%20knowledge%20of%20and%20experience%20in%20management%20and%20conduct%20of%20elections%2C%20can%20be%20appointed%20as%20ECs%20or%20CEC.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22104%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22101%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%5Cn%3Cp%3EX%5Cn%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2266%5C%22%3E6%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22331%5C%22%3ESearch%20Committee%20consisting%20of%20Cabinet%20Secretary%20and%20two%20other%20Secretaries%20to%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20shall%20prepare%20a%20panel%20of%20five%20persons%20for%20consideration%20of%20the%20Selection%20Committee%2C%20for%20appointment%20as%20CEC%20and%20ECs.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22104%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22101%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%5Cn%3Cp%3EX%5Cn%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2266%5C%22%3E7%20(1)%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22331%5C%22%3ESelection%20Committee%20will%20consist%20of%E2%80%94%20(a)%20Prime%20Minister%3B%20(b)%20the%20Leader%20of%20Opposition%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%3B%20and%20(c)%20a%20Union%20Cabinet%20Minister%20to%20be%20nominated%20by%20the%20PM.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22104%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22101%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%5Cn%3Cp%3EX%5Cn%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2266%5C%22%3E7(2)%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22331%5C%22%3EAppointment%20of%20CEC%20and%20other%20ECs%20shall%20not%20be%20invalid%20merely%20by%20reason%20of%20any%20vacancy%20in%20or%20any%20defect%20in%20the%20constitution%20of%20the%20Selection%20Committee.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22104%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22101%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%5Cn%3Cp%3EX%5Cn%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2266%5C%22%3E8(2)%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22331%5C%22%3EThe%20Selection%20Committee%20may%20also%20consider%20any%20other%20person%20than%20those%20included%20in%20the%20panel%20by%20the%20Search%20Committee.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22104%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22101%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%5Cn%3Cp%3EX%5Cn%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2266%5C%22%3E9(2)%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22331%5C%22%3EThe%20CEC%20and%20ECs%20shall%20not%20be%20eligible%20for%20re-appointment.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22104%5C%22%3EX%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22101%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2266%5C%22%3E9(3)%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22331%5C%22%3EWhere%20an%20EC%20is%20appointed%20as%20CEC%2C%20his%20term%20of%20office%20shall%20not%20be%20more%20than%20six%20years%20in%20aggregate%20as%20the%20EC%20and%20CEC%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22104%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22101%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%5Cn%3Cp%3EX%5Cn%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2266%5C%22%3E10(1)%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22331%5C%22%3EThe%20salary%2C%20allowances%20and%20other%20conditions%20of%20service%20of%20the%20CEC%20and%20other%20ECs%20shall%20be%20the%20same%20as%20those%20of%20the%20Cabinet%20Secretary%3A%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22104%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22101%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%5Cn%3Cp%3EX%5Cn%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2266%5C%22%3E10(5)%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22331%5C%22%3EWhere%20the%20CEC%20or%20an%20EC%20had%20retired%20from%20the%20service%20of%20the%20Central%20Govt%20or%20a%20State%20Govt%20prior%20to%20appointment%20as%20such%2C%20the%20aggregate%20period%20for%20which%20the%20encashment%20of%20unutilised%20earned%20leave%20he%20shall%20be%20entitled%20to%2C%20shall%20be%20subject%20to%20a%20maximum%20period%20as%20admissible%20to%20the%20Cabinet%20Secretary.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22104%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22101%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%5Cn%3Cp%3EX%5Cn%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2266%5C%22%3E11(2)%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22331%5C%22%3EThe%20CEC%20and%20ECs%20shall%20not%20be%20removed%20except%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20provisions%20contained%20in%20the%20first%20and%20second%20provisos%20respectively%20of%20clause%20(5)%20of%20article%20324%20of%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22104%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%5Cn%3Cp%3EX%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22101%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2266%5C%22%3E15%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22331%5C%22%3ESave%20as%20otherwise%20provided%20in%20this%20Act%2C%20the%20conditions%20of%20service%20relating%20to%20travelling%20allowance%2C%20medical%20facilities%2C%20leave%20travel%20concession%2C%20conveyance%20facilities%2C%20and%20such%20other%20conditions%20of%20service%20as%20are%2C%20for%20the%20time%20being%2C%20applicable%20to%20the%20Cabinet%20Secretary%2C%20shall%20be%20applicable%20to%20the%20CEC%20and%20ECs.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22104%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22101%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%5Cn%3Cp%3EX%5Cn%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2266%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22331%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22104%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E2%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22101%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E9%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20can%20be%20seen%2C%20only%20two%20sections%20are%20likely%20to%20support%20the%20ECI%E2%80%99s%20independence%20whereas%20nine%20will%20work%20towards%20reducing%20it.%20The%20remaining%20sections%20are%20of%20a%20general%20nature%20which%20do%20not%20have%20any%20implications%20for%20the%20institution%E2%80%99s%20independence%2C%20or%20lack%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClearly%2C%20while%20the%20Bill%20observes%20the%20letter%20of%20the%20SC%20judgment%20by%20way%20of%20making%20a%20law%2C%20it%20overwhelmingly%2C%20if%20not%20completely%2C%20violates%20the%20spirit%20or%20the%20rationale%20for%20the%20judgment.%20As%20the%20court%20observes%20in%20para%20227%20of%20its%20judgment%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6it%20was%20intended%20all%20throughout%20that%20appointment%20exclusively%20by%20the%20Executive%20was%20to%20be%20a%20mere%20transient%20or%20stop%20gap%20arrangement%20and%20it%20was%20to%20be%20replaced%20by%20a%20law%20made%20by%20the%20Parliament%20taking%20away%20the%20exclusive%20power%20of%20the%20Executive.%20This%20conclusion%20is%20clear%20and%20inevitable%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBarriers%20to%20the%20exercise%20of%20independence%20by%20the%20ECI%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20providing%20for%20three%20levels%20of%20barriers%20in%20the%20Bill%2C%20the%20government%20has%20tried%20its%20best%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20Election%20Commission%20is%20not%20able%20to%20function%20independently%20under%20any%20circumstances%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EEligibility%20criteria%20for%20EC%20and%20CEC%20appointments%20(Section%205%20of%20the%20Bill)%3A%20Only%20%3C%2Fem%3Ecurrent%20and%20former%20secretaries%20to%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20(GoI)%2C%20that%20is%2C%20only%20those%20who%20have%20been%20part%20of%20the%20executive%20for%20long%20are%20to%20be%20considered%20for%20these%20positions.%20How%20independent%20can%20such%20persons%20be%20of%20the%20executive%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20opinion.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EProcedure%20for%20shortlisting%20candidates%20(Section%206%20of%20the%20Bill)%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20It%20will%20be%20a%20case%20of%20bureaucrats%20choosing%20bureaucrats%20%E2%80%93%20the%20search%20committee%20comprising%20the%20cabinet%20secretary%20and%20two%20other%20secretaries%20to%20the%20GoI%2C%20will%20shortlist%20as%20EC%20and%20CEC%20hopefuls%2C%20persons%20who%20have%20been%20diehard%20members%20of%20the%20executive%20for%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20composition%20of%20the%20selection%20committee%20(Section%207(1)%20of%20the%20Bill)%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20Whereas%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%20had%20suggested%20a%20committee%20comprising%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition%2C%20and%20the%20chief%20justice%20of%20India%2C%20the%20Bill%20replaces%20the%20non-executive%20element%20of%20the%20chief%20justice%20of%20India%20with%20%E2%80%9Ca%20Union%20Cabinet%20Minister%20to%20be%20nominated%20by%20the%20PM.%E2%80%9D%20With%20two%20of%20the%20three%20members%20of%20the%20selection%20committee%20hailing%20from%20the%20executive%2C%20how%20can%20anyone%20even%20dream%20of%20an%20Election%20Commission%20acting%20independent%20of%20the%20executive!%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22%E2%80%98Umpire%20Cannot%20be%20Subordinate%20to%20Team%20Captain%E2%80%99%3A%20Election%20Commissioners%20Bill%20Raises%20Questions%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fumpire-cannot-be-subordinate-to-team-captain%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Umpire%20Cannot%20be%20Subordinate%20to%20Team%20Captain%E2%80%99%3A%20Election%20Commissioners%20Bill%20Raises%20Questions%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESeeing%20the%20judgment%20and%20the%20Bill%20in%20a%20larger%20context%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20must%20be%20said%20unambiguously%20that%20while%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%20of%20March%2002%2C%202023%2C%20was%20a%20distinct%20step%20forward%20for%20protecting%20democracy%20in%20the%20country%2C%20the%20proposed%20Bill%20takes%20two%20steps%20backward%20in%20that%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20also%20needs%20to%20point%20out%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20decision%20regarding%20the%20composition%20of%20the%20selection%20committee%20was%20possibly%20influenced%2C%20at%20least%20to%20some%20extent%2C%20by%20the%20prayers%20in%20the%20petitions%20before%20the%20court.%20%5BDisclosure%3A%20an%20organisation%20that%20this%20writer%20is%20associated%20with%2C%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20(ADR)%2C%20was%20one%20of%20the%20petitioners%20in%20the%20case%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%5D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20experience%20of%20appointments%20by%20similar%20collegiums%20or%20committees%20%E2%80%93%20of%20the%20director%2C%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%2C%20central%20information%20commissioners%20and%20chief%20information%20commissioner%2C%20among%20others%20%E2%80%93%20broadly%20shows%20that%20this%20method%20has%20not%20always%20resulted%20in%20the%20best%20possible%20or%20the%20most%20appropriate%20recommendations.%20Maybe%20there%20is%20a%20need%20to%20break%20new%20ground%20on%20this%20aspect.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%E2%80%99s%20suggestion%20regarding%20the%20need%20to%20break%20new%20ground%20is%20not%20meant%20to%20distract%20attention%20from%20the%20current%20task%20of%20opposing%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20Bill%20in%20both%20houses%20of%20Parliament.%20It%20goes%20without%20saying%20that%20the%20Bill%20is%20damaging%20to%20democracy%20and%20must%20be%20opposed%20at%20all%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20breaking%20new%20ground%20is%20necessary%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20criticality%20of%20the%20position%20of%20the%20ECI%2C%20the%20CEC%20and%20ECs%20in%20a%20democracy%20demonstrates%20the%20urgency%20for%20a%20new%20perspective%20on%20the%20issue.%20The%20criticality%20of%20the%20institution%20is%20clearly%20stated%20early%20on%20in%20the%20SC%20judgment%20(para%2041)%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20Election%20Commissioners%20stand%20on%20a%20%3Cem%3Efar%20higher%20pedestal%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20the%20constitutional%20scheme%20of%20things%20having%20regard%20to%20the%20relationship%20between%20their%20powers%2C%20%3Cem%3Efunctions%20and%20duties%20and%20the%20upholding%20of%20the%20democratic%20way%20of%20life%20of%20the%20nation%2C%20the%20upkeep%20of%20Rule%20of%20Law%20and%20the%20very%20immutable%20infusion%20of%20life%20into%20the%20grand%20guarantee%20of%20equality%3C%2Fem%3E%20under%20Article%2014%20(emphasis%20added).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20similar%20vein%2C%20the%20SC%20judgment%20also%20describes%20the%20uniqueness%20of%20Article%20324%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%20which%20provides%20for%20the%20establishment%20of%20the%20ECI%20(para%20219)%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20it%20is%20equally%20clear%20that%20Article%20324%20has%20a%20%3Cem%3Eunique%20background%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20Founding%20Fathers%20clearly%20contemplated%20a%20law%20by%20Parliament%20and%20%3Cem%3Edid%20not%20intend%20the%20executive%20exclusively%20calling%20the%20shots%20in%20the%20matter%20of%20appointments%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission%3C%2Fem%3E%20(emphasis%20added).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proposed%20Bill%20has%20been%20made%20in%20pursuance%20of%20Article%20324(2)%20of%20the%20Constitution%20which%20says%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20appointment%20of%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20other%20Election%20Commissioners%20shall%2C%20subject%20to%20the%20provisions%20of%20any%20law%20made%20in%20that%20behalf%20by%20Parliament%2C%20be%20made%20by%20the%20President%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20in%20this%20context%20that%20the%20court%20examines%20Article%20324(2)%20in%20depth%20in%20a%20section%20of%20the%20judgment%20titled%20%E2%80%98Articles%20in%20the%20Constitution%2C%20which%20employ%20the%20words%20%E2%80%9Csubject%20to%20any%20law%E2%80%9D%20to%20be%20made%20by%20Parliament%20as%20contained%20in%20Article%20324.%E2%80%99%20This%20examination%20in%20the%20judgment%2C%20from%20para%2034%20to%20para%2049%2C%20ends%20with%20the%20observation%2C%20%E2%80%9CNo%20further%20discussion%20is%20needed%20to%20conclude%20that%20Article%20324(2)%20is%20%3Cem%3Eunique%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20its%20setting%20and%20purpose%20(emphasis%20added)%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStressing%20the%20importance%20of%20the%20ECs%E2%80%99%20role%2C%20the%20court%20observes%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20already%20elaborated%20and%20found%20that%20core%20values%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20including%20democracy%2C%20and%20Rule%20of%20Law%2C%20are%20being%20undermined.%20It%20is%20also%20intricately%20interlinked%20with%20the%20transgression%20of%20Articles%2014%20and%2019.%20Each%20time%2C%20on%20account%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98knave%E2%80%99%2C%20in%20the%20words%20of%20Dr.%20Ambedkar%2C%20or%20again%20in%20his%20words%2C%20%E2%80%98a%20person%20under%20the%20thumb%20of%20the%20Executive%E2%80%99%2C%20calls%20the%20shots%20in%20the%20matter%20of%20holding%20the%20elections%2C%20which%20constitutes%20the%20very%20heart%20of%20democracy%2C%20even%20formal%20democracy%2C%20which%20is%20indispensable%20for%20a%20Body%20Polity%20to%20answer%20the%20description%20of%20the%20word%20%E2%80%98democracy%E2%80%99%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%20(Para%20226).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20SC%20contrasts%20ECI%E2%80%99s%20uniqueness%20in%20contrast%20to%20that%20of%20the%20comptroller%20and%20auditor%20general%20of%20India%20while%20comparing%20Articles%20324%20(2)%20and%20148%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COn%20a%20comparison%20of%20both%20the%20Articles%2C%20the%20difference%20is%20stark%20and%20would%20justify%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20contention%20that%20in%20regard%20to%20the%20appointment%20of%20the%20Members%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%2C%20having%20regard%20to%20the%20overwhelming%20importance%20and%20the%20nearly%20infinite%20plenary%20powers%20%5B%2C%5D%20they%20have%20in%20regard%20to%20the%20most%20important%20aspect%20of%20democracy%20itself%2C%20viz.%2C%20the%20holding%20of%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%20%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%20(para%20228).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20finally%20concludes%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20%3Cem%3Eunique%3C%2Fem%3E%20nature%20of%20the%20provision%20%5BArticle%20324%20(2)%5D%20we%20are%20concerned%20with%20and%20the%20devastating%20effect%20of%20continuing%20to%20leave%20appointments%20in%20sole%20hands%20of%20the%20Executive%20on%20fundamental%20values%2C%20as%20also%20the%20Fundamental%20Rights%E2%80%A6%20(emphasis%20added).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20these%20very%20pointers%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20regarding%20the%20need%20to%20keep%20alive%20ECI%E2%80%99s%20uniqueness%20that%20have%20prompted%20one%20to%20think%20of%20a%20new%20perspective%20on%20the%20issue%2C%20of%20breaking%20new%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20so%E2%80%9D%20new%20ground%20for%20a%20fresh%20perspective%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20may%20surprise%20many%20that%20what%20one%20is%20referring%20to%20as%20%E2%80%98new%E2%80%99%20ground%20was%20actually%20explored%20by%20Constituent%20Assembly%20member%2C%20Professor%20Shibban%20Lal%20Saxena%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.constitutionofindia.net%2Fdebates%2F15-jun-1949%2F%5C%22%3Emoved%20an%20amendment%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20a%20proposal%20made%20by%20Dr%20B.R.%20Ambedkar.%20The%20significance%20of%20the%20amendment%20is%20such%20that%20it%20deserves%20to%20be%20quoted%20extensively%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMr.%20President%2C%20Sir%2C%20I%20must%20congratulate%20Dr.%20Ambedkar%20on%20moving%20his%20amendment.%20As%20he%20has%20said%2C%20his%20amendment%20really%20carries%20out%20the%20recommendations%20of%20the%20Fundamental%20Rights%20Committee%20and%20in%20fact%20the%20matter%20was%20so%20important%20that%20it%20was%20thought%20at%20one%20time%20that%20it%20should%20be%20included%20in%20the%20Fundamental%20Rights.%20The%20real%20purpose%20is%20that%20the%20fundamental%20right%20of%20adult%20franchise%20should%20not%20only%20be%20guaranteed%20in%20practice.%20He%20has%20explained%20to%20us%20that%20he%20has%20tried%20to%20make%20the%20Election%20Commission%20wholly%20independent%20of%20the%20Executive%20and%20he%20therefore%20hopes%20that%20by%20this%20method%20the%20fundamental%20right%20to%20franchise%20of%20all%20the%20individuals%20shall%20not%20only%20be%20guaranteed%20but%20that%20it%20shall%20also%20be%20exercised%20in%20a%20proper%20manner%20so%20that%20the%20elected%20People%20will%20represent%20the%20true%20will%20of%20the%20people%20of%20the%20country.%20After%20a%20careful%20study%20of%20his%20amendment%20I%20have%20suggested%20my%20above%20amendments%20to%20carry%20out%20the%20real%20purpose%20of%20Dr.%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20amendment%20in%20full.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20desired%20by%20my%20amendment%20is%20that%20the%20Election%20Commission%20shall%20be%20completely%20independent%20of%20the%20Executive.%20Of%20course%20it%20shall%20be%20completely%20independent%20of%20the%20provincial%20Executive%20but%20if%20the%20President%20is%20to%20appoint%20this%20Commission%2C%20naturally%20it%20means%20that%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20appoints%20this%20Commission.%20He%20will%20appoint%20the%20other%20Election%20Commissioners%20on%20his%20recommendations.%20Now%20this%20does%20not%20ensure%20their%20independence.%20Of%20course%20once%20he%20is%20appointed%20he%20shall%20not%20be%20removable%20except%20by%202%2F3rd%20majority%20of%20both%20the%20Houses.%20That%20is%20certainly%20something%20which%20can%20instil%20independence%20in%20him%2C%20but%20it%20is%20quite%20possible%20that%20some%20party%20in%20power%20who%20wants%20to%20win%20the%20next%20election%20may%20appoint%20a%20staunch%20party-man%20as%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner.%20He%20is%20removable%20only%20by%202%2F3rd%20majority%20of%20both%20Houses%20on%20grave%20charges%2C%20which%20means%20that%20he%20is%20almost%20irremovable.%20So%20what%20I%20want%20is%20this%20that%20even%20the%20person%20who%20is%20appointed%20originally%20should%20be%20such%20that%20he%20should%20be%20enjoying%20the%20confidence%20of%20all%20parties%E2%80%93his%20appointment%20should%20be%20confirmed%20not%20only%20by%20majority%20but%20by%20two-thirds%20majority%20of%20both%20the%20Houses.%20If%20it%20is%20only%20a%20bare%20majority%20then%20the%20party%20in%20power%20could%20vote%20confidence%20in%20him%20but%20when%20I%20want%202%2F3rd%20majority%20then%20it%20means%20that%20the%20other%20parties%20must%20also%20concur%20in%20the%20appointment%20so%20that%20in%20order%20that%20real%20independence%20of%C2%A0the%20commission%20may%20be%20guaranteed%2C%20in%20order%20that%20everyone%20even%20in%20Opposition%20may%20not%20have%20anything%20to%20say%20against%20the%20Commission%2C%20the%20appointments%20of%20the%20Commissioners%20and%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20must%20be%20by%20the%20President%20but%20the%20names%20proposed%20by%20him%20should%20be%20such%20as%20command%20the%20confidence%20of%20two-thirds%20majority%20of%20both%20the%20Houses%20of%20Legislatures.%20Then%20no%20person%20can%20come%20in%20who%20is%20a%20staunch%20party-man.%20He%20will%20necessarily%20have%20to%20be%20a%20man%20who%20will%20enjoy%20the%20confidence%20of%20not%20only%20one%20party%20but%20also%20of%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20members%20of%20the%20Legislature.%20Then%20alone%20he%20can%20get%20a%202%2F3rd%20majority%20in%20support%20of%20his%20appointments.%20I%20therefore%2C%20think%20that%20if%20the%20real%20purpose%20of%20the%20recommendations%20of%20the%20Fundamental%20Rights%20Committee%20is%20to%20be%20carried%20out%2C%20as%20Dr.%20Ambedkar%20proposes%20to%20do%20this%20by%20amendment%2C%20then%20he%20must%20provide%20that%20the%20appointment%20shall%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%20be%20by%20the%20president%20subject%20to%20confirmation%20by%20a%20two-thirds%20majority%20of%20both%20the%20Houses%20of%20Parliament%20sitting%20and%20voting%20in%20a%20joint%20session.%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20want%20that%20in%20future%2C%20no%20Prime%20Minister%20may%20abuse%20this%20right%2C%20and%20for%20this%20I%20want%20to%20provide%20that%20there%20should%20be%20two-thirds%20majority%20which%20should%20approve%20the%20nomination%20by%20the%20President.%20Of%20course%20there%20is%20danger%20where%20one%20party%20is%20in%20huge%20majority.%20As%20I%20said%20just%20now%20it%20is%20quite%20possible%20that%20if%20our%20Prime%20Minister%20wants%2C%20he%20can%20have%20a%20man%20of%20his%20own%20party%2C%20but%20I%20am%20sure%20he%20will%20not%20do%20it.%20Still%20if%20he%20does%20appoint%20a%20party-man%20and%20the%20appointment%20comes%20up%20for%20confirmation%20in%20a%20joint%20session%2C%20even%20a%20small%20opposition%20or%20even%20a%20few%20independent%20members%20can%20down%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20before%20the%20bar%20of%20public%20opinion%20in%20the%20world.%20Because%20we%20are%20in%20a%20majority%20we%20can%20have%20anything%20passed%20only%20theoretically.%20So%20the%20need%20for%20confirmation%20will%20invariably%20ensure%20a%20proper%20choice.%20Therefore%2C%20I%20hope%20this%20majority%20will%20not%20be%20used%20in%20a%20manner%20which%20is%20against%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20nation%20or%20which%20goes%20against%20the%20impartiality%20and%20independence%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission.%20I%20want%20that%20there%20should%20be%20provision%20in%20the%20Constitution%20so%20that%20even%20in%20the%20future%20if%20some%20Prime%20Minister%20tends%20to%20be%20partial%2C%20he%20should%20not%20be%20able%20to%20be%20so.%20Therefore%2C%20I%20want%20to%20provide%20that%20whenever%20such%20appointment%20is%20made%2C%20the%20person%20appointed%20should%20not%20be%20a%20nominee%20of%20the%20President%20but%20should%20enjoy%20the%20confidence%20of%20two-thirds%20majority%20of%20both%20the%20Houses%20of%20Parliament.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%20also%20quotes%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20member%E2%80%99s%20amendment%20with%20approval%20and%20notes%20that%20the%20amendment%20was%20not%20accepted%20because%20of%20opposition%20from%20some%20other%20members.%20The%20result%20was%20the%20existing%20Article%20324(2)%20saying%20that%20the%20President%20will%20appoint%20the%20CEC%20and%20ECs%20%E2%80%9Csubject%20to%20the%20provisions%20of%20any%20law%20made%20in%20that%20behalf%20by%20Parliament.%E2%80%9D%20The%20kind%20of%20Bill%20that%20has%20been%20introduced%20is%20proof%20of%20Constituent%20Assembly%20member%20Saxena%E2%80%99s%20foresight!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20citizen%E2%80%99s%20proposal%20for%20EC%20and%20CEC%20appointments%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20Constituent%20Assembly%20member%20Saxena%E2%80%99s%20lead%2C%20here%20is%20a%20proposal%20for%20a%20procedure%20to%20appoint%20the%20CEC%20and%20ECs%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1.%20An%20existing%20committee%20of%20parliament%20or%20a%20new%20committee%20formed%20for%20this%20purpose%20to%20propose%20the%20eligibility%20criteria%20for%20appointment%20as%20EC%2FCEC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2.%20The%20committee%E2%80%99s%20proposals%20would%20then%20be%20placed%20before%20parliament%2C%20requiring%20approval%20by%20two-thirds%20majority%20of%20the%20members%20of%20parliament%20present%20and%20voting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3.%20Once%20the%20eligibility%20criteria%20are%20approved%20by%20parliament%2C%20the%20same%20committee%20should%20be%20entrusted%20with%20the%20task%20of%20searching%20for%20and%20selecting%20individuals%20for%20the%20position%20of%20ECs%2FCEC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3.1%20The%20committee%20should%20invite%20nominations%20of%20and%20applications%20by%20individuals%20considered%20appropriate%20for%20and%20interested%20in%20being%20appointed%20as%20ECs%2FCEC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3.2%20Out%20of%20the%20nominations%20and%20applications%20received%2C%20the%20suitable%20candidates%20should%20be%20shortlisted%20by%20the%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3.3%20The%20interviews%20of%20short-listed%20aspirants%20by%20the%20committee%20should%20be%20conducted%20in%20open%20hearings%2C%20accessible%20for%20viewing%20by%20the%20general%20public%20through%20video-transmission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3.4%20After%20the%20hearings%2C%20the%20committee%20should%20select%20individuals%20proposed%20to%20be%20appointed%20as%20ECs%2FCEC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E4.%20The%20next%20stage%20would%20be%20for%20the%20committee%20to%20send%20its%20recommendations%20to%20parliament%20for%20consideration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E5.%20The%20committee%E2%80%99s%20recommendation%20should%20be%20considered%20approved%20by%20parliament%20only%20if%20approved%20by%20two-thirds%20of%20the%20members%20of%20parliament%20present%20and%20voting%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E6.%20Once%20approved%20by%20parliament%2C%20the%20recommendations%20should%20be%20sent%20to%20the%20President%20for%20assenting%20to%20the%20appointments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E7.%20Once%20appointed%2C%20such%20persons%20should%20occupy%20their%20positions%20for%20six%20years%20or%20the%20age%20of%2075%20years%20whichever%20is%20earlier.%20Persons%20above%20the%20age%20of%2069%20years%20should%20not%20be%20appointed%20so%20that%20each%20appointee%20has%20a%20tenure%20of%20six%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E8.%20The%20stipulations%20of%20point%207%20should%20apply%20to%20each%20appointment%20independently.%20Every%20EC%20should%20have%20a%20tenure%20of%20six%20years%20and%20every%20CEC%20should%20have%20a%20tenure%20of%20six%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECritics%20might%20say%20that%20the%20proposed%20system%20will%20be%20very%20time%20consuming%20and%20may%20even%20term%20it%20impractical.%20This%20may%20well%20be%20true%2C%20given%20the%20way%20parliament%20functions%2C%20or%20does%20not%20function%2C%20these%20days.%20But%20%3Cem%3Eif%20%3C%2Fem%3EIndia%20has%20to%20move%20towards%20a%20really%20functional%20and%20substantive%20democracy%2C%20parliament%20and%20parliamentarians%20have%20to%20learn%20to%20be%20responsible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20only%3C%2Fem%3E%20option%20if%20the%20uniqueness%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20and%20its%20critical%20role%20in%20sustaining%20democracy%20is%20recognised%20and%20accepted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EJagdeep%20S.%20Chhokar%20is%20a%20concerned%20citizen.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3C%2Ftbody%3E%3C%2Ftable%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693555257000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15125309%2FNirvachan-Sadan-TW.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felection-commission-appointments-its-time-to-go-back-to-the-future%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Beyond%20the%20binary%20of%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20ruling%20and%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20disquieting%20new%20Bill%20lies%20a%20fresh%20perspective%20on%20limiting%20executive%20control%20over%20EC%20appointments.%20This%20%E2%80%98new%E2%80%99%20perspective%20goes%20back%20to%20prescient%20Constituent%20Assembly%20debates.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felection-commission-appointments-its-time-to-go-back-to-the-future%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22New%20Bill%20Has%20Controversial%20Provision%3A%20President%E2%80%99s%20Call%20on%20Mercy%20Plea%20Final%2C%20Cannot%20Appeal%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F05%2F12171900%2FPrison-bars.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20new%20Bharatiya%20Nagarik%20Suraksha%20Sanhita%20Bill%20(BNSS)%2C%202023%20proposes%20that%20a%20death-row%20convict%20whose%20mercy%20petition%20has%20been%20disposed%20of%20by%20the%20president%20will%20have%20no%20right%20to%20appeal%20against%20the%20decision%2C%20PTI%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Flaw-today%2Fstory%2Fdeath-row-convict-cant-appeal-against-presidents-mercy-plea-order-bnss-bill-2429274-2023-08-31%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EArticle%2072%20of%20the%20Constitution%20empowers%20the%20president%20to%20grant%20pardons%2C%20reprieves%2C%20respites%20or%20remissions%20of%20punishment%20or%20to%20suspend%2C%20remit%20or%20commute%20the%20sentence%20of%20anyone%20convicted%20of%20any%20offence.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CNo%20appeal%20shall%20lie%20in%20any%20court%20against%20the%20order%20of%20the%20president%20made%20under%20Article%2072%20of%20the%20constitution%20and%20it%20shall%20be%20final%2C%20and%20any%20question%20as%20to%20the%20arriving%20of%20the%20decision%20by%20the%20President%20shall%20not%20be%20enquired%20into%20in%20any%20court%2C%E2%80%9D%20section%20473%2C%20an%20addition%20to%20the%20BNSS%20Bill%2C%20which%20proposes%20to%20replace%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%20(CrPC)%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Flaw-today%2Fstory%2Fdeath-row-convict-cant-appeal-against-presidents-mercy-plea-order-bnss-bill-2429274-2023-08-31%5C%22%3Eread%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20ruled%20in%20the%20past%20that%20the%20exercise%20of%20prerogative%20powers%2C%20such%20as%20clemency%20and%20pardons%2C%20by%20the%20president%20or%20the%20governor%20may%20be%20challenged%20in%20court.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20like%20that%20of%20Mumbai%20blast%20convict%20Yakub%20Memon%20and%20in%20the%20Nirbhaya%20case%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Flaw-today%2Fstory%2Fdeath-row-convict-cant-appeal-against-presidents-mercy-plea-order-bnss-bill-2429274-2023-08-31%5C%22%3Edeath%20row%20convicts%20approached%20the%20court%20at%20the%2011th%20hour%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20seeking%20a%20review%20of%20the%20president%E2%80%99s%20rejection%20of%20their%20mercy%20petitions.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20refused%20to%20stay%20the%20executions%20in%20both%20the%20cases.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20new%20bill%20also%20seeks%20to%20avoid%20a%20delay%20on%20account%20of%20separate%20pleas%20filed%20by%20multiple%20convicts%20in%20the%20same%20case%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20the%20proposed%20Bill%2C%20a%20jail%20superintendent%20shall%20ensure%20that%20every%20convict%2C%20in%20case%20there%20are%20more%20than%20one%20in%20a%20case%2C%20submits%20the%20mercy%20plea%20within%2060%20days%20and%20where%20no%20such%20petition%20is%20received%20from%20the%20other%20convicts%2C%20he%20shall%20himself%20send%20the%20names%2C%20addresses%2C%20copies%20of%20the%20case%20records%20and%20all%20other%20details%20to%20the%20Union%20or%20the%20state%20government%2C%20along%20with%20the%20original%20mercy%20petition%2C%20the%20report%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Flaw-today%2Fstory%2Fdeath-row-convict-cant-appeal-against-presidents-mercy-plea-order-bnss-bill-2429274-2023-08-31%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20president%20shall%20decide%20the%20petitions%20of%20all%20the%20convicts%20together.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EApart%20from%20specifying%20time-limits%20for%20filing%20mercy%20pleas%20in%20death-row%20cases%20with%20the%20governor%20(Article%20161)%20and%20the%20president%20(Article%2072)%2C%20section%20473%20of%20the%20BNSS%20Bill%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Flaw-today%2Fstory%2Fdeath-row-convict-cant-appeal-against-presidents-mercy-plea-order-bnss-bill-2429274-2023-08-31%5C%22%3Eseeks%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20give%20the%20Union%2060%20days%E2%80%99%20time%20from%20the%20date%20of%20receipt%20of%20the%20state%20government%E2%80%99s%20comments%20on%20the%20pleas%20to%20send%20its%20recommendation%20to%20the%20president.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20no%20time-limit%20has%20been%20specified%20for%20the%20president%20for%20disposing%20of%20the%20mercy%20petitions%2C%20the%20president%E2%80%99s%20decision%20on%20such%20a%20plea%20is%20sought%20to%20be%20communicated%20by%20the%20Union%20to%20the%20state%20home%20department%20and%20jail%20superintendent%20concerned%20within%2048%20hours%20of%20the%20disposal%2C%20the%20report%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Flaw-today%2Fstory%2Fdeath-row-convict-cant-appeal-against-presidents-mercy-plea-order-bnss-bill-2429274-2023-08-31%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693554356000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F05%2F12171900%2FPrison-bars.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fnew-bill-proposes-to-make-presidents-call-on-mercy-plea-final-to-reduce-judicial-delays%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20ruled%20in%20the%20past%20that%20the%20exercise%20of%20prerogative%20powers%2C%20such%20as%20clemency%20and%20pardons%2C%20by%20the%20president%20or%20the%20governor%20may%20be%20challenged%20in%20court.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fnew-bill-proposes-to-make-presidents-call-on-mercy-plea-final-to-reduce-judicial-delays%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Beacon%20of%20Hope'%3A%20What%20the%20Ramon%20Magsaysay%20Award%20Citation%20for%20Oncologist%20Ravi%20Kannan%20Says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F01112851%2FUntitled-design-9.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Surgical%20oncologist%20Ravi%20Kannan%20R.%20who%20heads%20the%20Cachar%20Cancer%20Hospital%20and%20Research%20Centre%20in%20Assam%20has%20been%20named%20one%20of%20the%20recipients%20of%20the%20Ramon%20Magsaysay%20Award%20for%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20annual%20awards%2C%20named%20after%20former%20Philippine%20president%20Ramon%20Magsaysay%2C%20are%20called%20%E2%80%98Asia%E2%80%99s%20Nobel%20prize%E2%80%99%20and%20are%20considered%20very%20prestigious.%20Earlier%20recipients%20from%20India%20include%20Satyajit%20Ray%2C%20Bezwada%20Wilson%20and%20Ravish%20Kumar%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20recipients%20this%20time%20are%20Bangladeshi%20educationist%20Korvi%20Rakshand%2C%20Timorese%20environmentalist%20Eugenio%20Lemos%2C%20and%20Filipino%20peace%20negotiator%20Miriam%20Coronel%20Ferrer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20citation%20for%20the%20award%20noted%20Kannan%E2%80%99s%20incredible%20contributions%20to%20healthcare.%20It%20noted%20that%20in%20%E2%80%9Cforgotten%E2%80%9D%20places%20like%20the%20northeast%20of%20India%2C%20where%20healthcare%20is%20often%20difficult%20or%20expensive%20to%20access%2C%20cancer%20is%20all%20the%20more%20emotionally%20and%20financially%20devastating%20for%20patients%20and%20their%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAssam%E2%80%99s%20first%20cancer%20hospital%20was%20not%20opened%20until%201981%2C%20and%20the%20second%2C%20the%20Cachar%20Cancer%20Hospital%20and%20Research%20Centre%20(CCHRC)%20was%20established%20in%201996.%20The%20citation%20notes%20that%20it%20was%20the%20initiative%20of%20a%20non-profit%20society%20of%20local%20citizens%2C%20funded%20by%20public%20philanthropy%20on%20land%20provided%20by%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20Kannan%20took%20over%20as%20its%20director%20in%202007%2C%20CCHRC%20grew%20into%20an%20%E2%80%9Cinnovative%2C%20widely%20admired%2C%20full-service%20cancer%20care%20facility%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20award%E2%80%99s%20citation%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20surprised%20many%20that%20Kannan%2C%20who%20previously%20headed%20the%20surgical%20oncology%20department%20in%20Adyar%20Cancer%20Institute%2C%20a%20major%20cancer%20institute%20in%20Chennai%2C%20would%20exchange%20a%20position%20in%20a%20big%20city%20for%20a%20small%20hospital%20in%20a%20remote%20part%20of%20the%20country.%20Kannan%20had%20a%20simple%20answer.%20It%20was%20where%20he%20was%20most%20needed.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKannan%E2%80%99s%20leadership%20led%20to%20CCHRC%20getting%2028%20departments%20covering%20oncology%2C%20pathology%2C%20radiology%2C%20microbiology%2C%20epidemiology%2C%20tumour%20registry%20and%20palliative%20care%2C%20and%20other%20services%20and%20specialisations.%20From%20a%20staff%20of%20only%20twenty-three%2C%20the%20hospital%20now%20employs%20451%20people%2C%20the%20award%E2%80%99s%20citation%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20includes%20the%20essential%20ways%20in%20which%20Kannan%20sought%20to%20ensure%20care%20reached%20he%20poor%2C%20who%20would%20often%20have%20to%20travel%20long%20distances%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThus%2C%20the%20hospital%20introduced%20such%20pro-poor%20initiatives%20as%20free%20treatment%2C%20food%20and%20lodging%2C%20adhoc%20employment%20for%20caregivers%2C%20and%20a%20homecare%20program.%20Hospital%20team%20members%20would%20travel%20long%20distances%20to%20train%20family%20members%20in%20pain%20management%20and%20palliative%20care%2C%20as%20well%20as%20provide%20free%20medicines.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20patient%20compliance%20rates%20rose%20to%2070%25.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CCHRC%20also%20provides%20free%20or%20subsidised%20cancer%20care%20treatments%20to%20an%20average%20of%205%2C000%20new%20patients%20annually%2C%20catering%20to%20approximately%2020%2C000%20poor%20patients%20for%20treatments%20and%20follow-ups.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPTI%20also%20reports%20that%20satellite%20clinics%20have%20been%20started%20in%20Karimganj%2C%20Hailakandi%2C%20and%20Dima%20Hasao%20districts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20the%20citation%20notes%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20electing%20Ravi%20Kannan%20R.%20to%20receive%20the%202023%20Ramon%20Magsaysay%20Award%2C%20the%20board%20of%20trustees%20recognizes%20his%20devotion%20to%20his%20profession%E2%80%99s%20highest%20ideals%20of%20public%20service%2C%20his%20combination%20of%20skill%2C%20commitment%2C%20and%20compassion%20in%20pushing%20the%20boundaries%20of%20people-centered%2C%20pro-poor%20health%20care%20and%20cancer%20care%2C%20and%20for%20having%20built%2C%20without%20expectation%20of%20reward%2C%20a%20beacon%20of%20hope%20for%20millions%20in%20the%20Indian%20state%20of%20Assam%2C%20thus%20setting%20a%20shining%20example%20for%20all.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693553400000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F01112851%2FUntitled-design-9.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Framon-magsaysay-ravi-kannan-cachar-hospital%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Kannan%20is%20a%20visionary%20medical%20professional%20and%20heads%20the%20Cachar%20Cancer%20Hospital%20and%20Research%20Centre%20in%20Assam%2C%20which%20took%20up%20enormous%20efforts%20to%20ensure%20care%20to%20the%20poor%20under%20his%20leadership.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Framon-magsaysay-ravi-kannan-cachar-hospital%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%E2%80%99s%20Crude%20Oil%20Imports%20from%20Russia%20Down%20by%2020%25%2C%20Saudi%20Oil%20is%20Back%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F28110029%2F11147221423_303ec1a1d8_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20India%E2%80%99s%20crude%20oil%20import%20in%20August%20has%20come%20down%20drastically.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20has%20fallen%20by%2020%25%20last%20month%2C%20down%20from%20120%20thousand%20per%20barrel%20a%20day%20(kbd)%20to%204.45%20million%20a%20barrel%20per%20day%20(mbd).%20This%20is%20due%20to%20a%20reduction%20in%20its%20controversial%20and%20much%20discussed%20oil%20import%20from%20Russia.%20The%20figures%20were%20put%20out%20by%20Vortexa%2C%20a%20London-based%20market%20intelligence%20provider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20had%20imported%202.1%20mbd%20from%20Russia%20in%20July%202023%2C%20but%20in%20August%2C%20it%20fell%20to%20the%20lowest%20amount%20in%20seven%20months%2C%20to%201.63%20mbd.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%E2%80%99s%20crude%20imports%20in%20July%20reached%20a%20three-month%20high%20of%204.58%20mbd.%20Strong%20domestic%20and%20exported%20crude%20oil%20demand%20had%20buoyed%20refiners%20to%20operate%20at%20high%20utilisation%20that%20month.%20In%20August%202023%2C%20lower%20crude%20imports%20from%20Russia%20saw%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20total%20imports%20retreat.%20At%20least%20two%20refineries%20have%20shut%20down%20for%20planned%20maintenance%2C%20and%20several%20more%20are%20scheduled%20over%20this%20quarter%20and%20next%2C%E2%80%9D%20Serena%20Huang%2C%20an%20analyst%20at%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fbusiness%2F2023%2Fsep%2F01%2Fcrude-oil-imports-from-russia-fell-20-in-august-2610629.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EVortexa%20is%20cited%20as%20saying%20by%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20New%20Indian%20Express.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETraditional%20suppliers%20to%20India%20of%20crude%20oil%2C%20West%20Asia%20mainly%2C%20appear%20to%20be%20back%20in%20business.%20Saudi%20Arabia%20has%20re-emerged%20as%20a%20key%20supplier%20of%20crude%20oil%20to%20India.%20India%E2%80%99s%20crude%20imports%20from%20Saudi%20Arabia%20rebounded%20by%2060%25%20month-on-month%20to%20840%20kbd%20in%20August.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98A%20depleting%20account%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20believed%20that%20the%20reason%20for%20the%20drop%20in%20imports%20from%20Russia%20is%20%E2%80%9Ca%20depleting%20discount.%E2%80%9D%20The%20discount%20on%20Russian%20oil%20is%20said%20to%20have%20fallen%20drastically%20from%20%2415%20a%20barrel%20to%20%245%20a%20barrel.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%E2%80%99s%20imports%20of%20Russian%20crude%20were%20down%20440%20kbd%20in%20August%20to%201.63%20mbd%2C%20and%20discounts%20on%20Russian%20Urals%20against%20dated%20Brent%20have%20narrowed%20on%20a%20FOB%20basis.%20Given%20higher%20dated%20Brent%20prices%20in%20recent%20weeks%2C%20this%20means%20that%20Russian%20Urals%20is%20now%20likely%20more%20expensive%20when%20sold%20on%20a%20DES%20basis%20to%20Indian%20refiners%2C%E2%80%9D%20Serene%20Huang%2C%20analyst%20at%20Vortexa%20is%20quoted%20as%20saying.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERecently%2C%20Russia%20announced%20voluntary%20output%20cuts%20of%20500%2C000%20barrels%20a%20day%20in%20August%20and%20300%2C000%20barrels%20a%20day%20in%20September%2C%20mainly%20of%20Urals%20grade%2C%20according%20to%20Russian%20officials.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERussia%20overcame%20EU%20ban%20due%20to%20Indian%20imports%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndian%20imports%20of%20Russian%20crude%20have%20made%20global%20news%2C%20as%20they%20helped%20Russia%20ride%20out%20the%20difficulties%20that%20the%20EU%20ban%20on%20Russian%20oil%20imposed%20in%20December%202022%20posed%20for%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EData%20on%20the%20discharge%20volume%20by%20destination%20ports%20in%20India%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vortexa.com%2Finsights%2Farticle%2Frussia-overcomes-eu-ban-with-record-high-crude-exports-to-india%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eaccording%20to%20Vortexa%20in%20January%20this%20year%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20revealed%20that%20private%20refiners%20have%20led%20the%20increase%20in%20Russian%20crude%20purchases.%20Their%20%E2%80%9Cshare%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20crude%20imports%20from%20Russia%20increased%20from%2040%25%20during%20July-November%20last%20year%2C%20to%2048%25%20in%20December%2C%20rising%20further%20to%2060%25%20in%20January.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2023%2F06%2F22%2Fbusiness%2Findia-russia-oil.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20June%20on%20the%20role%20of%20so-called%20certain%20%E2%80%98laundromat%E2%80%99%20countries%2C%20%E2%80%9Cchief%20among%20whom%20was%20India%2C%20as%20well%20as%20China%2C%20Turkey%2C%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%20and%20Singapore.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20cited%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenergyandcleanair.org%2Fpublication%2Fthe-laundromat-how-the-price-cap-coalition-whitewashes-russian-oil-in-third-countries%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereport%20in%20April%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20put%20out%20by%20the%20Centre%20for%20Research%20on%20Energy%20and%20Clean%20Air%2C%20a%20research%20group%20based%20in%20Finland.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20%E2%80%98laundromat%E2%80%99%20countries%20were%20ones%20that%20bought%20Russian%20oil%2C%20refined%20it%20into%20other%20products%20and%20sell%20it%20on%20to%20buyers%20in%20Europe%2C%20the%20United%20States%20and%20other%20jurisdictions%20that%20have%20halted%20direct%20purchases%20from%20Russia.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EControversies%20in%20India%20over%20Russian%20Oil%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOther%20than%20the%20role%20of%20private%20refiners%20cornering%20benefits%20of%20Russian%20oil%20imports%2C%20there%20was%20controversy%20over%20other%20aspects%20of%20Russian%20oil%20imports%20in%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20purported%20use%20of%20the%20Chinese%20Yuan%20to%20foot%20the%20bill%20for%20it%20to%20dodge%20the%20